## Project Structure

```
VisionGuard-Safety-AI/
├── configs/
│   └── config.yaml          # All paths, thresholds, and model settings
├── src/visionguard/
│   ├── detection/           # Object detection (workers, PPE, vehicles)
│   ├── tracking/            # Multi-object tracking (IDs, trajectories)
│   ├── safety/              # Safety rules (PPE, zones, falls)
│   ├── dashboard/           # Streamlit Safety Command Center
│   ├── reporting/           # PDF incident report generation
│   └── utils/               # Config loading, logging
├── tests/                   # Unit tests (pytest)
├── data/                    # Input videos & datasets (git-ignored)
├── models/                  # Model weights (git-ignored)
└── outputs/                 # Screenshots, clips, reports, logs (git-ignored)
```

## Setup

Requires **Python 3.11+**.

```bash
# 1. Clone and enter the project
git clone <repo-url>
cd VisionGuard-Safety-AI

# 2. Create and activate a virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate        # Windows
# source .venv/bin/activate   # Linux / macOS

# 3. Install dependencies + the visionguard package (editable)
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e .

# 4. Run the tests
pytest
```

All runtime settings (video source, model choice, thresholds) live in [`configs/config.yaml`](configs/config.yaml).

## Tech Stack

Detection **YOLO11** · Tracking **ByteTrack** · Pose **YOLO-Pose / MediaPipe** · Dashboard **Streamlit** · Reports **ReportLab** · Config **YAML + typed dataclasses** · Tests **pytest**

*(Stack sections are added here as each component lands.)*
